🚨 ONLINE TICKET SALES

Buy your tickets online at -

https://iphawks.ticketleap.com/

ADULTS (Visitor): $5
STUDENTS (Visitor): $3

🔺 Each ticket purchased online will have a processing fee from the ticket sales company.

🔺 NO RESERVED SEATING (General Admission Only) and NO PREGAME TICKETS will be sold on campuses for the home games.

🔺 Ticket sales will open to the public Tuesday morning at 8am for each home game and close Friday at 4pm the day of the game.

🔺 All tickets NOT SOLD online will be sold at the gate. It will be a first come first serve basis at the gate.

🚨 GATE SALES 🚨

ADULTS: $7
STUDENTS: $5

Ticket sales will open up the Mondays before all home games at 8am. Access to purchase tickets will be through a password, which will be given out to the varsity players, band, and cheer.

💥 Please spread the word 💥

HOLLIDAY GAME - AUGUST 28

Holliday is giving IPHS only 400 tickets. Each varsity athlete, band member, and cheerleader will be given two tickets. The tickets will be sold to those parents first in the IPHS office starting on Tuesday, August 25 at 9 AM until Thursday, August 27 at 3:30 PM.￼

If any additional tickets remain after giving the two tickets to each student, then those tickets will be sold on a first come first serve basis starting on Friday, August 28 at 9 AM in the IP HS office.￼

The number of additional tickets will be posted via High School FB page and High School website on Thursday evening.

Ticket Price: $4.00 each.

post_text: Just a reminder for those students that will be working remotely that will be needing a Chromebook!!
shared_text:
Iowa Park High School
August 15 at 10:20 AM ·

Chromebook Information for IPHS students:

Students that will be working remotely, you should have received a Skylert with the information below about picking up your chromebook. Students that will be working on campus will receive their chromebooks during the school day as usual. Chromebook insurance can now be paid through Skyward.

Students working remotely- Chromebook pickups will be held in the entryway foyer of the High School on Tuesday the 18th, from 8:00-12:00. Please wear a mask and observe social distancing when you enter. Chromebook insurance fees can be paid through your student’s Skyward account. Please fill out the form that was attached to the Skylert message and bring it with you.

If you are unable to pick up the Chromebook at that time, please contact Mrs. Miller at jmiller@ipcisd.net or call 940-592-2328.

Just a reminder if you have not already completed online registration for your student, please log on to Skyward and complete that ASAP. Once completed, you will be able to view your student's schedule.

Remember, however, that no schedule changes will be made until the first week of school. Your student will get a form to fill out that will then be turned into the Academic Coordinator. The student will need to follow the schedule in Skyward until they receive a new one.

Fish Camp sign up form for ONLY incoming 9th graders for Wednesday, August 19th! I just sent out a link via skylert for you to pick a time slot for your student. You will select a time for your 9th grader to come to get their schedule and let a senior show them their classes. ONLY the student (must be wearing a face covering) is allowed into the school at the selected time. Parents may wait in the car, as it will not take them very long. Please show up anytime during the 30-minute time slot you selected, but no earlier or later as there are other groups in those times. Here is the link if you didnt get it via skylert. post_text:
Incoming 9th grade parents!!
I’ve had several questions about Fish Camp!!
Yes, we still plan on having Fish Camp on Wednesday, August 19th but it will not be the traditional way. Due to COVID and social distancing we can’t have the camp we usually have. We plan on having the freshmen come at specific 30 minute time slots throughout the day to pick up a fish camp shirt, their schedule, and get a tour from our NHS/PALS seniors and meet their teachers.
The week prior, I will send out a link for you to pick a time slot for your kiddo. We look forward to meeting your child and for the 2020-2021 school year!

post_text:
Seniors and Parents,
We have been working to provide the maximum number of seats/tickets for each graduate given all of the restrictions. As you know, the state has specified that no more than 5 people may be in a family group (or pod) and that there must be 6 feet of space between each pod. After much work and measuring, we were able to ensure that each of our 120 graduates could have 2 pods each- which is a total of 10 tickets. Given the number of students, the dimensions of our stadium seating, as well as the regulations, what we came up with doesn’t leave much room, but we can make this work legally and safely. I wish we could make a larger number work, but logistics truly prevent it.

We will be assigning tickets based on a lottery system and will keep the assigned 2 pods near each other.

Further details will be coming soon.

Thank you!

post_text:
Information for Graduation 2020
Senior 2020 Graduates

Seniors and Parents,
Based on the new rulings concerning graduation provided by the Commissioner of Education yesterday, we are now able to schedule graduation. Our plan is as follows:

Date: June 5th (or June 6th if weather prevents the ceremony on the 5th)
Location: Hawk Stadium
Time: 8:00 p.m.
Practice: Practices are not permitted. We will contact students closer to time with details for the ceremony.
Attendee Numbers: According to state guidelines, only 5 household family members are allowed in a group. We are working to see if we can increase that number while still following the established guidelines of social distancing.

* Please remember that everything is still subject to change based on any new regulations provided by the Commissioner of Education and the Governor.
* Graduations that occur in counties that have had more than 5 cases of COVID are not permitted prior to June 1st per the Commissioner’s newest regulations.

GRADUATION AT HAWK STADIUM?
Iowa Park school trustees met Thursday night in a special session, and heard plans to hold the 2020 IPHS graduation in Hawk Stadium. Tentative dates are either May 22 or May 23 (and possibly into June), all depending on guidance from state and local authorities as the state continues to deal with the novel coronavirus pandemic. Stay tuned to the Iowa Park Leader for any updates. Current plans include safety restrictions laid out by Governor Abbott.

Iowa Park CISD
April 17 at 1:43 PM ·

Governor Abbott has extended the school closure through the end of the 2019-2020 school year. While we are saddened we won’t get to welcome our students and staff back to the school buildings, we will continue doing our best to provide for our students through the end of the school year.

📚 We will continue providing instruction in the same format we have been throughout the closure.

🥪 Grab and Go Meals will continue at Kidwell Elementary each day Monday-Thursday from 10:00 AM-12:00 PM. Thursday’s meals will include meals for Thursday AND Friday.

🎶 IPHS Prom is rescheduled for Saturday, July 18.

🎓 IPHS Graduation will take place at Memorial Auditorium at 4:00 on Saturday, July 25.

We appreciate the patience and work of teachers, students, and parents through this time. We will send reminders and updates as needed. We hope you all stay well and safe. Please communicate with your child’s teachers and campus administrators if you have questions or concerns. 💚

Jodi Henderson Schlaud
March 22 at 7:19 PM ·

I love Iowa Park Schools and all of the people who make up the IPCISD family. Administrators, technology, maintenance, food service, school board members, transportation, teachers, counselors, librarians, paraprofessionals, office staff, nurses, payroll, Human Resources, accounts payable, our school police force and especially our superintendent have been and will continue to work to do what is best for our awesome students. In the coming days and weeks, you will see the work of the amazing people who make your child’s school experience the best. We are all about to embark on a journey none of us were trained for but will take on without hesitation. Please show grace and keep these special people in your prayers. I promise they will be doing their very best for our students. They miss and love our students and will not take this lightly. I am so blessed and proud to be a Hawk...I have been since I was five years old.

Iowa Park CISD
March 16 at 3:09 PM ·

In an effort to keep the school community healthy, Iowa Park CISD will be cancelling school through the week of March 23-27. As of now, school will resume Monday, March 30. We will continue to monitor the situation daily and keep you informed of any further changes.

While we understand the hardship this puts on families, we also know practicing social distancing can help slow the spread of illness. We will be working hard to put together instructional packets for students to work on. These supports are intended to keep students engaged academically while we are on this extended break. More information on when and where to pick up packets will be coming soon.

We are thankful for the patience and understanding of our community. It is our hope that we all stay safe and healthy and that we can begin our lives as usual very soon! It is always a great day to be a Hawk!

Iowa Park CISD
March 12 at 3:13 PM ·

The health and safety of our students, staff, and community is a priority for the Iowa Park CISD. School officials have been and will continue to be in communication with state and county officials regarding COVID-19. Health authorities and the Texas Education Agency will provide guidance to the district as this situation evolves. Iowa Park CISD would like to remind the school community that the best ways to prevent the spread of the virus are the same preventions that are recommended for the spread of the flu and the common cold. Please see the press release below from the Wichita County Public Health District for more prevention information as well as information from the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC).

Thank you to URHCS for the fantastic day. Anatomy & Physiology students as well as some CNA students were able to go through rounds that included “Stop the Bleed”, “Hands Only CPR” (and Air Evac medical team teachings), plus a round with medical teams learning extremely valuable anatomical lessons that we could not and would not be able to get anywhere else. THANK YOU #URHCS!
And Thank You, students, for a great day!

🏈💚 Send-off for Football players 💚🏈

The High School will be on a normal bell schedule on Friday. We are not getting out early, however, there are a couple of things that will be happening:

We will have a “Sendoff for the FB players” combined with “Band Marching the Halls” @ 11:30.

Parents and Community are encouraged/invited/welcomed to help us line up in the Gym as the players walk through! The boys will NOT be leaving immediately- they will be going to the field house to load everything up!

AND…. Friday’s theme will be “Put the Wolves to sleep!” (Pajama Day)

post_text:
Attention IPHS Students & Staff!

Get your t-shirt for COLOR WARS 2019-2020!

For the coming school year at IPHS, we are offering t-shirts that students can purchase to go along with our annual color wars for homecoming. We will also be using the class colors throughout the year for class spirit days.

There is a color for each grade level. Seniors are pink, Juniors are purple, Sophomores are yellow, Freshmen are orange, and Staff are blue.

We will be selling them in two rounds. The first round will run from July 20th- July 29th with delivery to HS office the first week in August. The second round will run August 19th-30th with delivery the first part of September.

The link is below:

https://ipcolorwars2019.itemorder.com/product/10243345

post_text: NBA trainer Anthony Porter is coming to host a camp July 30th - 31st at Iowa Park HS. Cost is $100 for the 2 days. Camp will run from 10:00 - 3:00 both days. Boys and girls from 5th - 12th grade are welcome. Register online at www.anthonyporterbasketball.com/camps. Scroll to the bottom of the page and select the camp to register. Of you have any questions contact Coach Fields via email at gfields@ipcisd.net. Don't miss out on this great opportunity to grow your basketball game.

post_text: 🎶 IPHS took 4 choir members to TSSEC (UIL TX State Solo Ensemble Contest) and three came back with medals. Left to right, Andrew Morrow (12) earned a Division 1 rating (gold medal), Destiny Mitcham (12) earned a division 2 rating (silver medal), Micah Scobee (11) earned a division 1 rating (gold medal). Saydie Bradberry (12) received a division 3 rating. We are SO proud of them!!
